---
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout title="Immigration | ImmediateLawyerHelp.com">
<!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="heroBg" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="container heroInner">
      <div class="heroCard">
        <h1>Immigration</h1>
        <p class="heroSub">
          Immigration matters often involve strict forms, deadlines, and document requirements.
          Choose a topic below, or describe what you need help with to continue.
        </p>

        <form id="heroSearchForm" class="heroSearch" autocomplete="off">
          <input
            id="issueInput"
            type="text"
            placeholder="Briefly describe your immigration issue…"
            aria-label="Describe your immigration issue"
          />
          <button type="submit">Get Started</button>
        </form>

        <div class="heroBadges">
          <span>Confidential</span><span class="sep">•</span>
          <span>Time-sensitive</span><span class="sep">•</span>
          <span>Independent attorneys</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Article -->
  <section class="section sectionTight">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="card">
        <article class="immArticle">
          <h2 class="cardTitle">Common immigration matters</h2>
          <p class="muted" style="margin-top:10px; line-height:1.65; max-width:78ch;">
            Immigration cases can involve agency processing, interviews, supporting evidence, and changing rules.
            The sections below provide a quick overview and link to dedicated pages (coming soon).
          </p>

          <section class="immSection" id="green-card">
            <h3 class="immH"><a class="immTitleLink" href="/immigration/green-card/">General Immigration / Green Card</a></h3>
            <div class="immImage">
              <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1529070538774-1843cb3265df?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=60" alt="" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <p class="guideMeta immBlurb">
              Green card and general immigration matters can include family-based petitions, adjustment of status, consular processing, and evidence preparation.
              These cases often depend on accurate paperwork, supporting documents, and meeting eligibility requirements.
              Small errors can create delays, so organizing documents early usually helps.
            </p>
            <a class="immLearn" href="/immigration/green-card/">Learn more →</a>
          </section>

          <section class="immSection" id="deportation">
            <h3 class="immH"><a class="immTitleLink" href="/immigration/deportation/">Deportation</a></h3>
            <div class="immImage">
              <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1523413651479-597eb2da0ad6?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=60" alt="" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <p class="guideMeta immBlurb">
              Deportation (removal) matters can involve immigration court hearings, bond issues, and requests for relief from removal.
              Deadlines and court dates can be strict, and missing one can have serious consequences.
              Having a clear timeline of events and copies of all notices is often important.
            </p>
            <a class="immLearn" href="/immigration/deportation/">Learn more →</a>
          </section>

          <section class="immSection" id="asylum">
            <h3 class="immH"><a class="immTitleLink" href="/immigration/asylum/">Asylum</a></h3>
            <div class="immImage">
              <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1455849318743-b2233052fcff?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=60" alt="" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <p class="guideMeta immBlurb">
              Asylum cases may involve preparing declarations, gathering evidence, and meeting filing deadlines.
              These matters can be emotionally demanding and documentation-heavy, often requiring careful organization.
              Understanding the process early can help reduce uncertainty about what’s required.
            </p>
            <a class="immLearn" href="/immigration/asylum/">Learn more →</a>
          </section>

          <section class="immSection" id="work-visas">
            <h3 class="immH"><a class="immTitleLink" href="/immigration/work-visas/">Work Visas</a></h3>
            <div class="immImage">
              <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521737604893-d14cc237f11d?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=60" alt="" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <p class="guideMeta immBlurb">
              Work visas can involve employer sponsorship, eligibility requirements, and time-limited filing windows.
              The process may include petitions, supporting evidence, and coordination with employers or schools.
              A clear understanding of visa category rules can prevent avoidable delays.
            </p>
            <a class="immLearn" href="/immigration/work-visas/">Learn more →</a>
          </section>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Keep sideSearchForm present -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container twoCol">
      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="cardTitle">Not sure which applies?</h2>
        <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.6; max-width:72ch;">
          Describe your immigration issue and we’ll route you to the right next step.
        </p>

        <form id="sideSearchForm" class="sideSearch" autocomplete="off">
          <input type="text" placeholder="Describe your issue…" aria-label="Describe your issue" />
          <button type="submit" aria-label="Search">→</button>
        </form>
      </div>

      <aside class="card">
        <h2 class="cardTitle">Notes</h2>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>Information on this site is not legal advice.</li>
          <li>Using this site does not create an attorney-client relationship.</li>
          <li>Independent attorneys may have different availability and policies.</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    /* Immigration page-specific styling: restrained images, article rhythm */
    .immArticle .immSection{
      padding: 18px 0 34px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);
    }
    .immArticle .immSection:last-of-type{
      border-bottom: 0;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .immH{
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 18px;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .immTitleLink{
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .immTitleLink:hover{
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
    .immImage{
      margin: 12px 0 18px;
      border-radius: 14px;
      overflow: hidden;
      max-width: 62%;
    }
    .immImage img{
      width: 100%;
      height: 140px;
      object-fit: cover;
      display: block;
      filter: saturate(.9) contrast(.95);
    }
    @media (max-width: 900px){
      .immImage{ max-width: 100%; }
    }
    .immBlurb{
      margin-top: 10px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      max-width: 78ch;
    }
    .immLearn{
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      margin-top: 12px;
      padding: 10px 12px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,.04);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.10);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 650;
    }
    .immLearn:hover{
      background: rgba(255,255,255,.06);
      border-color: rgba(255,255,255,.14);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
